com.kaazing.gateway.jms.client

Class JmsConnectionFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kaazing.gateway.jms.client.JmsConnectionFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javax.jms.ConnectionFactory

    public abstract class JmsConnectionFactory
extends Object
implements javax.jms.ConnectionFactory
    JMS Client implementation of . Used to create a connection with a JMS provider via a WebSocket connection. Also provides the ability to set the Gateway location dynamically.

      • getWebSocketFactory

        public WebSocketFactory getWebSocketFactory()
        Returns the instance of underlying WebSocketFactory that is used to create and establish WebSocket connection to send/receive data over WebSocket connection. The WebSocketFactory instance can be used to set default characteristics. For example, an application developer can use it to set the ChallengeHandler to perform authentication.
        Returns:
        instance of WebSocketFactory

      • setWebSocketFactory

        public void setWebSocketFactory(WebSocketFactory webSocketFactory)
        Sets the WebSocketFactory that will be used to create and establish WebSocket connection to send/receive data over WebSocket connection. When JmsConnectionFactory is created, the WebSocketFactory is implicitly created. The function can be used to replace the default WebSocketFactory. Application developer can create WebSocketFactory externally, enable extensions, set parameter values and can provide that WebSocketFactory to the JmsConnectionFactory.
        Parameters:
        webSocketFactory - Instance of WebSocketFactory

      • createConnection

        public javax.jms.Connection createConnection(String clientID)
                                      throws javax.jms.JMSException
        Creates a JMS Connection via WebSocket, using the default username and password to authenticate with the Gateway, and using the given clientID to distinguish the durable subscribers for this connection from those of other users.
        Parameters:
        clientID - Client identifier. This is combined with durable subscriber names, using the format specified for "jms" service parameter "client.durable.name.format", to make them unique for the current user
        Throws:
        javax.jms.JMSException
